// C2: Acting Components
instance PermanentMagnetSynchronousMotor : DTDFVocab:ActingComponent [
    base:desc "Primary actuator component integrated with cycloidal gear transmission system for rotational motion conversion. Driven by control mechanisms with bidirectional data flow capabilities for closed-loop operation."
]

instance CycloidalGearMechanism : DTDFVocab:ActingComponent [
    base:desc "Mechanical transmission system coupled with the PermanentMagnetSynchronousMotor to translate rotational motion with optimized torque characteristics for friction modeling applications."
]

// C3: Physical sensing components
instance MotorShaftPositionEncoder : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "High-precision position encoder mounted directly on the motor shaft capturing input angle data with sub-millimeter resolution for real-time monitoring."
    DTDFVocab:producedData MotorShaftPositionData
]

instance GearboxOutputPositionEncoder : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "Secondary position encoder positioned behind the cycloidal gearbox measuring output angle with high-resolution capabilities for transmission monitoring."
    DTDFVocab:producedData GearboxOutputPositionData
]

instance InputCurrentSensor : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "Current sensor integrated with the motor drive unit capturing real-time input current data for power analysis and control validation."
    DTDFVocab:producedData InputCurrentData
]

// C4: Physical-to-virtual interaction
instance MotorShaftPositionData : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom MotorShaftPositionEncoder
]

instance GearboxOutputPositionData : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom GearboxOutputPositionEncoder
]

instance InputCurrentData : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom InputCurrentSensor
]

// C10: Models/Data
instance SysMLInternalBlockDiagram : DTDFVocab:Model [
    base:desc "SysML IBD representing component-connector architecture of the physical system including PermanentMagnetSynchronousMotor and CycloidalGearMechanism with explicit interface definitions."
    DTDFVocab:inputTo SysMLModelingEnabler
]

instance MontiArcComponentModel : DTDFVocab:Model [
    base:desc "MontiArc component-connector model describing system behavior through MontiArc Automaton state machines for dynamic system representation."
    DTDFVocab:inputTo MontiArcEnabler
]

instance MathWorksSimulinkBehaviorModel : DTDFVocab:Model [
    base:desc "Behavioral simulation model created in MathWorks Simulink for detailed performance analysis of the system's functional and physical layers."
    DTDFVocab:inputTo SimulinkSimulationEnabler
]

instance AADLComponentSpecification : DTDFVocab:Model [
    base:desc "AADL specification defining component-based system architecture with timing and behavioral annotations for the motor-gearbox system."
    DTDFVocab:inputTo AADLEngineeringEnabler
]

instance ContextualDataTraceAggregation : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "Aggregated contextual data traces from physical sensors including position measurements and current data, abstracted for specific analytical purposes."
    DTDFVocab:fromData MotorShaftPositionData, GearboxOutputPositionData, InputCurrentData
    DTDFVocab:inputTo DataAggregationEnabler
]

instance SimulationInputData : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "Processed data inputs for simulation models including calibrated sensor readings and derived parameters for behavioral analysis."
    DTDFVocab:fromData ContextualDataTraceAggregation
    DTDFVocab:inputTo SimulinkSimulationEnabler, MontiArcEnabler
]

// C11: Enablers
instance SysMLModelingEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "SysML-based modeling platform enabling multi-layered system modeling across requirements, functional, logical, and product layers using Internal Block Diagrams."
    DTDFVocab:enables SysMLModelValidationService, SysMLArchitectureAnalysisService
]

instance MontiArcEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "MontiArc toolchain supporting component-connector modeling and state machine automation for system behavior representation."
    DTDFVocab:enables MontiArcBehaviorSimulationService
]

instance SimulinkSimulationEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "MathWorks Simulink environment for detailed behavioral modeling and dynamic system simulation integration with architecture description languages."
    DTDFVocab:enables SimulationBasedPredictionService, ControlValidationService
]

instance AADLEngineeringEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "AADL-based engineering platform for component-based system modeling with timing and behavioral annotations for the motor-gearbox system."
    DTDFVocab:enables AADLComponentValidationService
]

instance DataAggregationEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Cross-tool integration framework aggregating heterogeneous data sources including MQTT streams and simulation outputs for contextual analysis."
    DTDFVocab:enables DataTraceAbstractionService
]

instance MQTTDataStreamingEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "MQTT-based real-time data streaming protocol facilitating bidirectional communication between physical sensors and digital twin components."
    DTDFVocab:enables RealTimeMonitoringService
]

// C6: Services
instance SysMLModelValidationService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service validating SysML architecture models against requirements and functional specifications using formal verification techniques."
    DTDFVocab:provides ModelValidationInsight
]

instance SysMLArchitectureAnalysisService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service analyzing SysML Internal Block Diagrams to identify component interactions and interface dependencies."
    DTDFVocab:provides ArchitectureInsight
]

instance MontiArcBehaviorSimulationService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service simulating system behavior using MontiArc Automaton state machines for dynamic response analysis."
    DTDFVocab:provides BehavioralSimulationInsight
]

instance SimulationBasedPredictionService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service predicting system states and performance metrics using simulation models correlated with real-time sensor data."
    DTDFVocab:provides PredictiveAnalysisInsight
]

instance ControlValidationService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service validating control parameters and feedback mechanisms through simulation against real-time data streams."
    DTDFVocab:provides ControlAccuracyInsight
]

instance DataTraceAbstractionService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service abstracting contextual data traces for specific analytical purposes while maintaining traceability to physical measurements."
    DTDFVocab:provides DataAbstractionInsight
]

instance RealTimeMonitoringService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service providing real-time monitoring of physical system parameters through MQTT-based data streams."
    DTDFVocab:provides OperationalMonitoringInsight
]

instance AADLComponentValidationService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service validating AADL component specifications against timing and behavioral requirements for system integration."
    DTDFVocab:provides ComponentValidationInsight
]

// C17: Insights/Actions
instance ModelValidationInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Insight validating SysML architecture models against specified requirements and functional constraints through formal verification."
]

instance ArchitectureInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Insight identifying component interactions and interface dependencies within the SysML Internal Block Diagram architecture."
]

instance BehavioralSimulationInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Insight analyzing system behavior through MontiArc Automaton state machine simulations for dynamic response validation."
]

instance PredictiveAnalysisInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Insight forecasting system states and potential performance degradation based on simulation models correlated with real-time data."
]

instance ControlAccuracyInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Insight validating control parameter effectiveness through simulation-based validation against real-time sensor feedback."
]

instance DataAbstractionInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Insight providing purpose-driven abstraction of contextual data traces while maintaining traceability to physical measurements."
]

instance OperationalMonitoringInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Insight monitoring real-time operational parameters through MQTT-based data streams for immediate system assessment."
]

instance ComponentValidationInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Insight validating AADL component specifications against timing and behavioral requirements for system integration."
]

// C18: Actions
instance ValidateModelAction : DTDFVocab:Action [
    base:desc "Automated action validating SysML architecture models against requirements specifications."
    DTDFVocab:IsAutomatic true
]

instance AnalyzeArchitectureAction : DTDFVocab:Action [
    base:desc "Automated action analyzing component interactions within the SysML Internal Block Diagram."
    DTDFVocab:IsAutomatic true
]

instance SimulateBehaviorAction : DTDFVocab:Action [
    base:desc "Automated action simulating system behavior using MontiArc Automaton state machines."
    DTDFVocab:IsAutomatic true
]

instance PredictSystemStateAction : DTDFVocab:Action [
    base:desc "Automated action predicting system states based on simulation models and real-time data."
    DTDFVocab:IsAutomatic true
]

instance ValidateControlParametersAction : DTDFVocab:Action [
    base:desc "Automated action validating control parameters through simulation-based validation."
    DTDFVocab:IsAutomatic true
]

instance AbstractDataTracesAction : DTDFVocab:Action [
    base:desc "Automated action abstracting contextual data traces for specific analytical purposes."
    DTDFVocab:IsAutomatic true
]

instance MonitorOperationalParametersAction : DTDFVocab:Action [
    base:desc "Automated action monitoring real-time operational parameters through MQTT streams."
    DTDFVocab:IsAutomatic true
]

instance ValidateComponentSpecsAction : DTDFVocab:Action [
    base:desc "Automated action validating AADL component specifications against requirements."
    DTDFVocab:IsAutomatic true
]

// C19: Environment
instance ManufacturingEnvironment : DTDFVocab:Environment [
    base:desc "Operational environment for the digital twin system focused on manufacturing processes with industrial standards compliance."
    base:contains PermanentMagnetSynchronousMotor, CycloidalGearMechanism, MotorShaftPositionEncoder, GearboxOutputPositionEncoder, InputCurrentSensor
]

// C20: Components
instance MotorGearboxSystem : DTDFVocab:Component [
    base:desc "Physical component system consisting of PermanentMagnetSynchronousMotor integrated with CycloidalGearMechanism for rotational motion conversion in manufacturing applications."
    base:isContainedIn ManufacturingEnvironment
]

instance DigitalShadowRepresentation : DTDFVocab:Component [
    base:desc "Passive digital representation of the physical system aggregating contextual data traces for monitoring and analysis purposes without bidirectional control capabilities."
    base:isContainedIn ManufacturingEnvironment
]

instance DigitalTwinExtension : DTDFVocab:Component [
    base:desc "Active digital twin extension providing simulation, prediction, and decision support services through bidirectional data flows with the physical system."
    base:isContainedIn ManufacturingEnvironment
]

instance twinning_time_scale : DTDFVocab:TimeScale [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin system described in the provided documents operates within a **real-time, data-driven paradigm**, where sensor data is continuously streamed via **MQTT** for live monitoring and analysis. The temporal granularity is dictated by the **sensor-based measurements**, which are aggregated and abstracted for specific purposes (e.g., friction identification for a robot axis). While explicit synchronization frequencies (e.g., Hz, ms) or latency requirements are not quantified, the system relies on **automated one-way data flow** between physical and digital components, implying low-latency processing to maintain alignment with the physical system's operational time scale. The aggregation and abstraction of data traces occur in a **passive, context-aware manner**, ensuring the digital representation reflects the physical state with minimal delay for downstream applications. No explicit mention of fine-grained control over latency or aggregation delays is provided in the documents."
]

instance dt_constellation : DTDFVocab:Constellation [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin system's **orchestration and coordination** are framed within **Model-Based Systems Engineering (MBSE)** frameworks, leveraging **architecture description languages (ADLs)** like **SysML IBDs**, **MontiArc**, and **AADL** to define **component-based architectures** with explicit **interfaces, connectors, and composition rules**. The **MontiArc Automaton** and **SysML state machines** enable **behavioral coordination** at the logical level, while integration with **simulation tools** (e.g., **Simulink**) and **general-purpose languages** (e.g., **C++/Java**) supports **runtime orchestration**. The **digital shadow reference model** (Fig. 1) implies **passive data aggregation** but does not extend to active twin coordination. **Resource management** is implied via **MBSE toolchain integration**, though no **specific orchestration patterns** (e.g., microservices, event-driven, or service-oriented architectures) are mentioned. The **heterogeneous stakeholder integration** requirement (Section II.A) suggests **cross-cutting coordination mechanisms**, but **system-wide governance** (e.g., API gateways, middleware, or twin registry frameworks) is not detailed."
]

instance life_cycle_stages : DTDFVocab:EvolutionStage [
    base:desc "The lifecycle of a Digital Twin (DT) system is structured through **Model-Based Systems Engineering (MBSE)** methodologies, encompassing multiple abstraction layers: **requirements, functional architecture, logical architecture, and product/technical layers**. Transition management between these stages is facilitated by **architecture description languages (ADLs)** such as **ACME, AADL, MontiArc, or SysML Internal Block Diagrams (IBDs)**, which define components, interfaces, connectors, and composition hierarchies. Behavior modeling is augmented via **state machines in SysML v1.7** or **MontiArc Automaton**, while detailed simulations are integrated using tools like **MathWorks Simulink** or other simulation frameworks. Lifecycle governance involves **heterogeneous stakeholder integration** (e.g., engineering, operations, analytics teams) and **multi-tool interoperability**, ensuring seamless transitions between modeling notations (e.g., SysML for architecture, C++/Java for low-level behavior). The lifecycle is iterative, with **abstraction refinement** at each stage to align digital representations with physical system evolution."
]

instance fidelity_and_validity_considerations : DTDFVocab:FidelityConsideration [
    base:desc "The system employs **validation through comparative analysis** of **reference values** (physical measurements) and **simulated values** (derived from SysML/Simulink models) to assess model fidelity, particularly for **friction characterization**. Uncertainty quantification is implied through the **comparison of simulated and real-world data**, though explicit error detection or correction mechanisms are not described. The **passive nature of the Digital Shadow** ensures no closed-loop control or adaptive model updates, as the system **does not push data back to the physical system**. Quality assurance processes are not detailed beyond the **comparison-based validation**, which serves as the primary method for ensuring model accuracy in friction analysis."
]

instance dt_technical_connection : DTDFVocab:TechnicalConnection [
    base:desc "The document explicitly describes the **digital shadow** as a passive entity that does not include **two-way communication flows** (e.g., control commands, feedback loops, or bidirectional data exchange). Therefore, no technical connection details for **virtual-to-physical interaction** (e.g., command types, control message formats, validation mechanisms, or feedback systems) are provided. The only mentioned communication protocol for **physical-to-virtual interaction** is **MQTT**, with no details on network topology, redundancy, or security protocols for bidirectional communication. The system does not support **active control** or **conflict resolution** mechanisms as it is defined as a one-way data flow system."
]

instance horizontal_integration : DTDFVocab:HoriIntegration [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin system integrates horizontally with **external sensor systems** via **MQTT**, enabling real-time streaming of time-series data from sensors to the digital representation. No other interoperability standards (e.g., OPC UA, REST APIs) or external enterprise systems (PLM, ERP, MES) are referenced in the documents. The integration is **sensor-centric**, relying on live measurements to populate the digital twin's data traces. While the system exchanges data with external sources (e.g., sensor networks), the scope of integration is limited to **direct sensor-to-digital twin communication** without explicit mention of broader enterprise or IoT ecosystem dependencies. The lack of detailed protocols or standards beyond MQTT suggests a **domain-specific focus** on friction identification for robotic applications."
]

instance security_and_safety_considerations : DTDFVocab:SecuritySafety [
    base:desc "
The **safety cell** of the robotic system (as referenced in [44]) enforces physical safety by restricting the maximum working range of the robotic arm (MABI Max-100) to predefined operational zones, mitigating collision risks. The system leverages **MQTT (Message Queuing Telemetry Transport)** for real-time data streaming ([52]), which inherently supports lightweight publish-subscribe communication, though no explicit cybersecurity protocols (e.g., TLS encryption, authentication) are documented for this channel in the provided sources. No formal **access control mechanisms**, **threat mitigation strategies**, or **functional safety standards** (e.g., ISO 26262, IEC 61508) are mentioned in the documents. The **Asset Administration Shell (AAS)** framework ([46], [47], [50]) is noted for enabling traceability of data origin and linking live data, but no details on **cybersecurity protocols** (e.g., OAuth, JWT) or **privacy-preserving measures** (e.g., data anonymization, consent management) are provided. The context does not include **risk assessment approaches** or **safety-critical system considerations** beyond the physical safety cell."
]